# BMC Helix Java Process Activity — Build & Deploy Checklist

## AR System Platform Quirks (Must-Know Before Writing Code)

These are undocumented or poorly documented behaviors discovered through trial and error. Violating any of these causes runtime failures that are invisible at compile time.

### DateTime Handling

- [ ] **All date/time field values MUST use epoch milliseconds** (e.g., `System.currentTimeMillis()` or `Instant.now().toEpochMilli()`), NOT ISO 8601 strings
- [ ] Never use `Instant.now().toString()` or `LocalDateTime.toString()` for AR System date fields — this causes `ERROR 12095`

```java
// WRONG — causes ERROR 12095
fieldInstances.put("3", Instant.now().toString());          // "2026-02-18T10:30:00Z"

// CORRECT
fieldInstances.put("3", String.valueOf(System.currentTimeMillis()));  // "1771408200000"
```

### Required System Fields on Record Creation

- [ ] **Every record creation MUST set Status (field 7) and Description/Short Description (field 8)** explicitly
- [ ] Missing these fields causes silent failures or `ERROR 307` — records may appear created but with broken state

```java
// REQUIRED on every RecordInstance creation
fieldInstances.put("7", "0");    // Status — set to a valid status value
fieldInstances.put("8", ".");    // Short Description — can be a placeholder dot
```

### Transaction Annotations

- [ ] **`@RxDefinitionTransactional` MUST only be placed on REST endpoint methods**, NOT on internal service methods
- [ ] Internal services called by IS Rules or Processes already run inside a platform-managed transaction — adding the annotation causes `ERROR 12004` (transaction conflict)
- [ ] If you get `ERROR 8790` (transaction not started) on a REST endpoint, that endpoint DOES need `@RxDefinitionTransactional`

```java
// CORRECT — annotation on REST endpoint only
@Action(name = "MyRestEndpoint")
@RxDefinitionTransactional
public MyResponsePayload execute(@ActionParameter(...) String input) {
    // Call internal services here — they inherit this transaction
    myInternalService.doWork(input);
}

// WRONG — annotation on internal service called by a Rule
@RxDefinitionTransactional  // REMOVE THIS -- the Rule already has a transaction
public void doWork(String input) { ... }
```

### IS Rules Behavior

- [ ] **Rules fire only once per triggering event** — do NOT design batch processing loops that rely on rules firing repeatedly
- [ ] If processing gets stuck at 0%, check whether you're relying on a rule to iteratively process records — inline the processing logic instead
- [ ] For batch processing, iterate within a single service method rather than expecting rules to chain

### File Attachments

- [ ] `persistAttachment()` MUST be called AFTER the parent record is created, not before
- [ ] Setting a FileAttachment field as REQUIRED on the record definition will cause `ERROR 307` because the attachment cannot exist before the record
- [ ] Workflow: create record > get record ID > persist attachment > update record with attachment reference

### Record Creation via API

- [ ] Verify all REQUIRED fields on the record definition are populated before calling create
- [ ] AR System required fields are not always obvious — check the record definition in Innovation Studio
- [ ] Field 8 (Short Description) is commonly required even if not explicitly marked

