## Build Optimization Tips

### Backend-Only Changes

When only Java code has changed (no Angular modifications):
```bash
# Skip the Angular/frontend build entirely — saves ~2 minutes per cycle
docker exec bmc-helix-innovation-studio bash -c \
  "cd /workspace/sample-app && mvn clean install -Pdeploy -DskipTests -PskipUICodeGeneration"
```

### Incremental Development Strategy

- [ ] **Deploy early, deploy often** — don't generate all services before your first deployment
- [ ] Test each new service individually before creating the next one
- [ ] Feed runtime errors back to the AI immediately — it learns from each error and applies fixes across the codebase
- [ ] Keep a running list of every error and its fix — the AI will reference them for future services

### Build Cycle Awareness

Each build-deploy cycle takes ~3 minutes. With 10+ iterations common for first-time flows, expect **30–40 minutes of build wait time**. Plan accordingly:
- Fix as many issues as possible per cycle (batch fixes)
- Use `mvn clean install -DskipTests` (no `-Pdeploy`) for compilation-only checks when unsure about code correctness
- Only deploy when confident the fix is correct

