## Quick Reference — Full Workflow

```
 0. Review AR System Platform Quirks  (datetime, transactions, required fields, attachments)
 1. Create/edit Java files on HOST
 2. Verify files visible in DOCKER    (docker exec ... ls)
 3. If stale, docker cp files in      (docker cp ... bmc-helix-innovation-studio:...)
 4. Build and deploy                  (mvn clean install -Pdeploy -DskipTests)
    — Backend-only?                   (add -PskipUICodeGeneration to save ~2 min)
 5. Verify classes in JAR             (jar tf ... | grep ClassName)
 6. Verify AjcClosure1 exists        (confirms AspectJ weaving)
 7. Check deploy status               (Final Status: Deployed)
 8. Clear browser cache               (Cmd+Shift+R)
 9. Check Process Designer            (inside a process > add Process Activity)
10. If runtime error, fix and repeat  (batch multiple fixes per cycle when possible)
```

---

## AR System Error Code Quick Reference

| Error Code | Meaning | Common Fix |
|------------|---------|------------|
| ERROR 307 | Required field blank or attachment before record exists | Set Status(7) + Description(8); persist attachments after record creation |
| ERROR 930 | Action type not found on server | Deploy JAR first, then .def files separately |
| ERROR 8790 | Transaction not started | Add `@RxDefinitionTransactional` on REST endpoint |
| ERROR 12004 | Transaction conflict | Remove `@RxDefinitionTransactional` from internal service (Rule already has one) |
| ERROR 12095 | Invalid date format | Use epoch millis, not ISO 8601 |
